Functional Requirements (What the system MUST do)

The system shall allow users to register.
The system shall allow users to login.
The system shall allow users to submit complaints.
The system shall allow admins to update complaint status.
The system shall allow users to track complaints.

## User Side Requirements

* User must be able to **register**
* User must be able to **login**
* User must be able to **submit a complaint**
* User must be able to **upload supporting files (optional)**
* User must be able to **track complaint status**
* User must receive **status updates**
* User must be able to **view complaint history**

## Admin Side Requirements

* Admin must login securely
* Admin must view all complaints
* Admin must filter complaints (Pending / Resolved / In Progress)
* Admin must update complaint status
* Admin must respond to complaints
* Admin must maintain centralized dashboard

Non-Functional Requirements (How the system should behave)

The system shall respond within 3 seconds.
The system shall ensure secure login authentication.
The system shall support at least 100 concurrent users.

* System should be user-friendly
* Should allow real-time tracking
* Should improve transparency
* Should be scalable
* Should be maintainable
* Must be web-based
* Should handle multiple users
* Secure authentication 
* Fast response time

User Requirements (What users expect)

Normal User expects:
* Easy complaint submission
* Clear status visibility
* Fast response
* No complicated UI

Admin expects:
* Organized dashboard
* Easy filtering
* Quick status update option
* Clear complaint details


